text: I loved Jurassic Park and I thought
Laura Dern was super cool it really
scared me though and I used to sleep on
the top bunk so the dinosaurs couldn't
get to me but then slowly I realized how
big they were and that in fact I should
sleep under the bed so I think I did
that for a little while I worked with a
Canadian actress named Molly Parker who
is amazing and he's been in so many
amazing Canadian films and she really
inspired me as cheesy as it sounds and I
played a character for the first time
that kind of required an element of
emotional maturity I guess or depth or
transcendence or something and for the
first time feeling that and then just
wanting to feel that again and again and
to work with an actress whose
performance have been just utterly
fearless I don't know she was just so
cool it was one of those situations you
know I was like 15 I was just like how
cool is this person
